    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.11.10b" />
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <p>HRL</p>
                    </figure>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        At Home,
                        February 3, 1924.
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Doctor Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I thank you for your very kind and sympathetic letter and for your permission to use your approval of "Bol&#233;var". Its publication before my dear wife's death was a great pleasure to her and very gratifying to me. I wish you had known her. She was especially a very noble and upright woman and, even at her advanced age, of wonderfully attractive presence. An Omaha (Neb.) friend of 
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">10</fw>
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.11.10a"/>
                    
                    hers wrote me a beautiful letter in which she said that she always thought of my wife as a "marquise". Well, as you wrote, I have got to knuckle down and endure, and I thank you for your words of advice and comfort.</p>
                
                <p>My son, daughter-in-law and grand-daughter are with me and will probably remain, at least until he finishes the course at the War College in June.</p>
                
                <p><del>Vice</del><add>Ex-</add>president Wilson died to-day. What a wonderful opportunity this man had! But I think he missed it by being too aristocratic and self-centred.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Most faitfully yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed><hi rend="underline">H.R. Lemly.</hi></signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
